biolockj.module.implicit.parser.wgs

Class Humann2Parser

  • java.lang.Object
    • biolockj.module.BioModuleImpl
      • biolockj.module.ScriptModuleImpl
        • biolockj.module.JavaModuleImpl
          • biolockj.module.implicit.parser.ParserModuleImpl
            • biolockj.module.implicit.parser.wgs.Humann2Parser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BioModule, ParserModule, JavaModule, ScriptModule, Comparable<BioModule>

    public class Humann2Parser
extends ParserModuleImpl
implements ParserModule
    This BioModules parses Humann2Classifier output reports to build standard OTU abundance tables.
    Samples IDs are found in the column headers starting with the 2nd column.
    The count type depends on the HumanN2 config properties.
    GUI Module Name
    HumanN2 Parser

      • parseSamples

        public void parseSamples()
                  throws Exception
        To parse the taxonomy level reports output by Humann2Classifier. Sample HumanN2 report line (head output_pAbund.tsv):
        1st cell format: [Pathway_ID]:[Pathway_Descr] | g__[genus_taxa].s__[species_taxa]
        Example: ARO-PWY: chorismate biosynthesis I|g__Acidaminococcus.s__Acidaminococcus_intestini #SampleID Metaphlan22_Analysis #clade_name relative_abundance coverage average_genome_length_in_the_clade estimated_number_of_reads_from_the_clade k__Bacteria|p__Bacteroidetes 14.68863 0.137144143537 4234739 580770
        Specified by:
        parseSamples in interface ParserModule
